The paper proposes a new algorithm that combines Swarm Intelligence and Evolutionary mechanisms to solve dynamic optimization and environment extrema tracking problems. This makes it likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses bio-inspired ant-like agents, which suggests it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also deals with control problems, which could place it in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The use of optimization techniques and comparisons with other approaches suggest it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with tracking moving peaks, which could place it in the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
